## рҹ‘Ө Rootless Docker & User Namespace Remapping


### Rootless Docker


```text
в”Ңв”Җ Container в”Җв”җ          в”Ңв”Җ Host в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  root (0)   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ  dockremap user     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  process    в”Ӯ  remap   в”Ӯ  (UID 100000)       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ             в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–әв”Ӯ                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  uid 1000   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ  UID 101000         в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ          в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

User namespace remapping:
  dockerd --userns-remap=default
  Container root вҶ’ host dockremap (usually UID 65536+)
```

```bash
# Enable user namespace remapping
echo '{"userns-remap":"default"}' > /etc/docker/daemon.json
systemctl restart docker

# Rootless mode (no root daemon at all)
dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install
export DOCKER_HOST=unix:///run/user/$UID/docker.sock
```

### Caveats


```text
- Cannot share namespaces (--net=host, --pid=host) with host
- --privileged is ignored
- May break volume mount permissions (UID shifted)
- Some storage drivers not supported (devicemapper)
```

